  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment (expanded envelope)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). NOTE: The operating envelope was expanded in Q4 2025 to include paediatric patient populations (body surface area 0.5–1.2 m²) and low-flow pulsatile assist regimes (1.0–2.5 L/min) not covered by the original 2023 validation campaign. Re-validation against the expanded envelope is planned but has not yet been completed; existing validation evidence predates the expansion.",
